         <abstract>
            <p>Theatrical manuscripts have long been a matter of indifference to theatre specialists, and one of embarrassment to geneticists. One of the reasons for these difficulties is the multiplicity of the theatrical manuscript. The present proposed typology identifies thirteen relevant types.</p>
         </abstract>
